# ğŸ‘¤ PERSON 1 â€” Word Severity Levels

### `Severity.java`

```java
public enum Severity {
    LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH
}
```

### `Action.java`

```java
public enum Action {
    ALLOW, FLAG, BLOCK
}
```

### `SeverityEngine.java`

```java
public class SeverityEngine {

    public Action decideAction(Severity severity) {
        switch (severity) {
            case HIGH:
                return Action.BLOCK;
            case MEDIUM:
                return Action.FLAG;
            case LOW:
            default:
                return Action.ALLOW;
        }
    }
}
```

---

# ğŸ‘¤ PERSON 2 â€” Case-Insensitive & Partial Matching

### `TextMatcher.java`

```java
public class TextMatcher {

    public boolean containsBadWord(String text, String badWord) {
        String normalizedText = normalize(text);
        String normalizedBadWord = normalize(badWord);
        return normalizedText.contains(normalizedBadWord);
    }

    private String normalize(String input) {
        return input.toLowerCase().replaceAll("[^a-z]", "");
    }
}
```

---

# ğŸ‘¤ PERSON 3 â€” Strike & Context Rules

### `StrikeManager.java`

```java
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class StrikeManager {

    private Map<String, Integer> userStrikes = new HashMap<>();

    public Action applyStrike(String userId, Action baseAction) {
        int strikes = userStrikes.getOrDefault(userId, 0);

        if (baseAction == Action.ALLOW) {
            return Action.ALLOW;
        }

        strikes++;
        userStrikes.put(userId, strikes);

        if (strikes == 1) return Action.FLAG;
        if (strikes == 2) return Action.BLOCK;
        return Action.BLOCK; // permanent block simulated
    }
}
```

### `ContextRuleEngine.java`

```java
public class ContextRuleEngine {

    public boolean isAllowedInContext(String context, Severity severity) {
        if (context.equalsIgnoreCase("educational")) {
            return severity != Severity.HIGH;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

